2 SECTION 9. IC 15-15-1-27, AS AMENDED BY P.L.10-2022,
3 SECTION 1, AND P.L.33-2022, SECTION 1, IS AMENDED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 27. (a) The
5 state seed commissioner shall administer this chapter. The state seed
6 commissioner may authorize an agent to act for the state seed
7 commissioner under this chapter.
8 (b) The state seed commissioner may do any of the following to
9 administer this chapter:
10 (1) Sample, inspect, analyze, and test agricultural seed and
11 vegetable seed distributed within Indiana for seeding and sowing
12 purposes, when, where, and to the extent the state seed
13 commissioner considers necessary to determine whether the
14 agricultural seed or vegetable seed is in compliance with this
15 chapter.
16 (2) Notify a seed distributor of any violations of this chapter.
17 (3) Adopt rules:
18 (A) governing:
19 (i) methods of sampling, inspecting, analyzing, testing, and
20 examining agricultural seed and vegetable seed; and
21 (ii) tolerances to be followed in the administration of this
22 chapter; and
23 (B) necessary for the efficient enforcement of this chapter.
24 (4) Adopt rules to establish lists of prohibited noxious weeds and
25 restricted noxious weeds.
26 (5) Subject to section 28 of this chapter, adopt rules to establish
27 reasonable standards of germination (as defined by rule adopted
28 under section 28 of this chapter) for agricultural seed and
29 vegetable seed.
30 (6) Adopt rules to establish standards for the effectiveness of
31 legume inoculant applied to pre-inoculated seed.
32 (7) Adopt rules to govern the treatment of seed and the labeling
33 and distribution of treated seed.
34 (8) Publish at least one (1) time each year, in the form the seed
35 commissioner considers proper, information concerning:
36 (A) the sales of agricultural seed and vegetable seed; and
37 (B) the results of the analysis of official samples of
38 agricultural seed and vegetable seed sold within Indiana as
39 compared with the analysis guaranteed on the label.
40 Information concerning production and use of agricultural seed
41 and vegetable seed may not disclose the operation of any person.
42 (9) Enter any:
2026 IN 1192—LS 6703/DI 148

4
1 (A) public or private property during regular business hours;
2 or
3 (B) vehicle that transports seed, whether by land, water, or air,
4 at any time the vehicle is accessible;
5 to inspect seed and the records relating to the seed, subject to this
6 chapter and the rules adopted under this chapter.
7 (10) As used in this subdivision, "stop sale order" refers to a
8 written order issued by the state seed commissioner to the owner
9 or custodian of a lot of agricultural seed or vegetable seed that the
10 state seed commissioner has found violates this chapter or rules
11 adopted under this chapter. The state seed commissioner may
12 issue and enforce stop sale orders. A stop sale order prohibits the
13 future sale, processing, and movement of the seed until the state
14 seed commissioner issues a release from the stop sale order. The
15 owner or custodian of the seed is entitled to appeal a stop sale
16 order to a court with jurisdiction in the locality in which the seed
17 is found, as provided in IC 4-21.5, seeking a judgment as to the
18 justification for the order for the discharge of the seed from the
19 stop sale order in accordance with the findings of the court. This
20 subdivision does not limit the right of the state seed commissioner
21 to proceed as otherwise authorized by this chapter.
22 (11) Establish and maintain or make provisions for seed testing
23 facilities.
24 (12) Employ qualified persons.
25 (13) Incur necessary expenses.
26 (14) Test or provide for testing seed for purity (as defined by 7
27 CFR 201.2(w)) and germination (as defined by rule adopted
28 under section 28 of this chapter) for farmers and dealers on
29 request of a farmer or dealer and:
30 (A) prescribe rules governing such testing; and
31 (B) charge for the tests made.
32 Without adopting a rule, the state seed commissioner shall charge
33 fees that are commensurate with fees that are standard in the seed
34 testing industry.
35 (15) Cooperate with the United States Department of Agriculture
36 and other agencies in seed law enforcement.
37 (16) Enter the property of a producer of hybrid seed to determine
38 whether the seed produced is as the seed is represented.
39 (17) Subject to subsection (c), issue a written special use permit
40 to a person to use a prohibited noxious weed seed or a restricted
41 noxious weed seed for purposes of research, development,
42 production, or education. subject to subsection (c).
