7
1 the seed.
2 (B) The seed is sold and delivered to the purchaser on the
3 property on which the seed is grown.
4 (C) The seed does not contain prohibited noxious weed seed.
5 (D) The seed contains not more than one-fourth of one percent
6 (0.25%) of restricted noxious weed seed.
7 (E) The seed contains not more than two and one-half percent
8 (2.5%) of all weed seed.
9 If seed is advertised for sale through the medium of the public
10 press, by circular, by catalog, or by exposing a sample of the seed
11 or a printed or written statement about the seed in a public place
12 or place of business, or if the seed is delivered by a common
13 carrier, (except when transported for the purpose of being
14 recleaned as provided in this section), the producer is considered
15 to be a vendor, and the seed must meet all requirements of this
16 chapter, including complete labeling of the seed. For cereal and
17 soybean seed where the purpose for which the seed is intended
18 may be in question, seed advertised for sale by variety name, as
19 processed, tested, treated, or offered at a price substantially higher
20 than current market prices, is presumed to be offered for seeding
21 purposes and subject to the labeling provisions of this chapter.
22 (b) A person is not subject to the penalties of this chapter for
23 distributing agricultural seed or vegetable seed incorrectly labeled or
24 represented as to kind, variety, or origin and that cannot be identified
25 by examination of the seed unless the person fails to:
26 (1) obtain an invoice, genuine grower's declaration, or other
27 labeling information; and
28 (2) take other precautions reasonable to ensure the identity of the
