41 SECTION 15. IC 15-15-1-32, AS AMENDED BY P.L.75-2010,
42 SECTION 6, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
2026 IN 1192—LS 6703/DI 148

8
1 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 32. (a) A container of agricultural seed of any size
2 consisting of more than one (1) pound distributed in Indiana for sowing
3 and seeding purposes must contain or have attached in a conspicuous
4 place on the outside of the container a plainly written or printed tag or
5 label in English giving the information required by this section. If the
6 seed is distributed in bulk, the information required by this section
7 must accompany delivery and be supplied to the purchaser at the time
8 of delivery.
9 (b) The labeling required for seed sold in bags and packages, and in
10 bulk as required by this section, must include the following statements
11 on the labeling attached to the container:
12 (1) The commonly accepted name of each kind and variety of
13 each agricultural seed component that exceeds five percent (5%)
14 of the whole and the percentage by weight of each in the order of
15 its predominance. However, the variety designation may be
16 omitted if the label states the name of the kind and the words
17 "variety not stated". If more than one (1) component is required
18 to be named, the word "mixture" or the word "mixed" must be
19 shown conspicuously on the label. A mixture consisting of two (2)
20 or more varieties of the same kind may be designated as a
21 "blend".
22 (2) Lot number or other lot identification.
23 (3) Origin (state or foreign country where grown) for all seed
24 except hybrid corn. If the origin is unknown, that fact must be
25 stated.
26 (4) The percentage of all weed seed.
27 (5) The name and rate of occurrence per pound of each kind of
28 restricted noxious weed seed present.
29 (6) The percentage of all other agricultural seed or vegetable
30 seed, which may be designated as "other crop seeds" or "crop
31 seeds".
32 (7) The percentage of inert matter.
33 (8) For each named agricultural seed:
34 (A) the percentage of germination (as defined by rule adopted
35 provided under section 28 of this chapter), exclusive of hard
36 seed;
37 (B) the percentage of hard seed, if present; and
38 (C) the calendar month and year the test was completed to
39 determine the percentages.
40 (9) The name and address of the person who labeled the seed or
41 who distributed it within Indiana.
42 (10) For all seed named and treated (for which a separate label
2026 IN 1192—LS 6703/DI 148

9
1 may be used):
2 (A) a word or statement indicating that the seed has been
3 treated;
4 (B) the commonly accepted coined chemical or abbreviated
5 chemical (generic) name of any applied pesticide;
6 (C) a description of the process or the commonly accepted
7 name of the substance applied if other than a pesticide; and
8 (D) if the substance in the amount present with the seed is
9 harmful to human or other vertebrate animals, a caution
10 statement such as "Do Not Use For Food Or Feed Or Oil
