27 SECTION 16. IC 15-15-1-32.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
28 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
29 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 32.5. (a) Any agricultural seed
30 that remains in the inventory of a distributor after the germination
31 test has expired must be removed from sale or relabeled. The new
32 germination and hard seed claim, if applicable, along with the new
33 germination test date updated on the original label in a manner:
34 (1) that is clearly legible; and
35 (2) in which the old data is completely covered or obliterated.
36 (b) The person upon whose premises the seed is located is
37 responsible for obtaining the new test and for subsequent
38 relabeling of the seed.
